b'Office of Research'
b'Created in 2015 as a result of the University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford\xe2\x80\x99s strategic planning process, the Office of Research\xe2\x80\x99s mission is to increase student and faculty research productivity through the development of infrastructure and the provision of research opportunities needed for students and faculty.'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'SERVICES\xc2\xa0'
b'Ask a Biostatistician'
b'Kay\xc3\xa9romi Gomez, PhD, Biostatistician The biostatistician position is new to the UICOMR campus.'
b'As Biostatistician for the Office of Research, Dr. Kay\xc3\xa9romi Gomez provides support and assistance to faculty and students who are conducting research in the College of Medicine and the College of Pharmacy in the areas of study design, data analysis and interpretation of results. The purpose of the \xe2\x80\x9cAsk a Biostatistician\xe2\x80\x9d form is to provide a venue for medical and pharmacy students and faculty the opportunity to ask Dr. Gomez a biostatistics or research question that may need a quick answer. In this way, students and faculty are not limited to having to meet in-person on certain dates and times with Dr. Gomez to get help. If more in-depth help is needed, please email Dr. Gomez (kayeromi@uic.edu) to schedule a meeting to discuss your biostatistics/research needs.'
b'Ask a Biostatistician'
b'kayeromi@uic.edu'
b'Ask a Biostatistician Form'
b'PROGRAMS'
b'James Scholar Program\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x93 The James Scholar Program is an honors program targeting the top 25% of medical students. \xc2\xa0Over the course of three years, selected students, in partnership with a faculty research mentor, pursue and complete an independent research project based on their unique interests. \xc2\xa0Students are allotted a small budget for research expenses as well as travel costs associated with presenting their project at a national conference. \xc2\xa0Annually, 30 \xe2\x80\x93 35 medical students participate in the program.Research Day\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x93 Research Day is held annually on the UIC Health Sciences Campus Rockford. \xc2\xa0The event highlights the research and scholarly activities of students, residents and faculty of the College of Medicine and affiliated parnters. \xc2\xa0Research Day is coordinated by the College of Medicine Rockford committee on research.'
b'Student & Resident Research Travel Award\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x93 The Student & Resident Travel Award is awarded to a medical student or resident who is presenting as a first author at a national conference. \xc2\xa0Up to $1,000 in reimbursement in conference registration and travel expenses.'
b'Student & Resident Research Travel Award'
b'Walter Rice Craig Fellowship\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x93 The Walter Rice Craig Fellowship Program enables two medical students to engage in research under the guidance of a University of Illinois College of Medicine Rockford (UICOMR) faculty member the summer between their M1 and M2 year. \xc2\xa0The research must be conducted at UICOMR. \xc2\xa0Students are eligible to receive a $2,700 stipend and are expected to work on their project during the summer months. \xc2\xa0Students will present their project at the UICOMR\xe2\x80\x99s annual Research Day.'
b'FUNDING MECHANISMS'
b'Bridge Funding\xc2\xa0\xe2\x80\x93 Bridge funding is intended to provide short term financial support to sustain the research programs, laboratories, and momentum of productive researchers during funding gaps to give them a chance to regain extramural funding. \xc2\xa0Bridge funding is targeted to all members of the faculty of the College of Medicine Rockford who have established projects that demonstrate high probablility of securing extramural funding.'
b'Basic Research Bridge Funding Guidelines'
b'Basic Research Bridge Funding Application'
b'Faculty Application Instructions'
b'Student Application Instructions'
b'Clinical, Educational & Community Health Research Grant Application'
